node.title: Company Admits Selling N95 Masks to Grocery Chain at 400 Percent Markup, Faces Steep Fine
node.description: TSC Agency pled guilty to paying $1.09 per N95 mask and selling them to a grocery store chain for $5.25. They face fines of $200,000 or more.

node.title: Southwest Says it Will Return to Profitability in 4th Quarter After $135M Loss Last Quarter
node.description: "With any luck, last quarter was our last losing quarter," Southwest CEO Gary Kelly told analysts during an investor event in New York.

node.title: David Banks, Educator and Adams Ally, Is Next N.Y.C. Schools Chancellor
node.description: Mr. Banks, who founded the Eagle Academy, a network of public schools for boys, is the first commissioner named to Mayor-elect Eric Adams’s administration.

node.title: Joe Biden Signs Executive Order to Make Federal Government Carbon-Neutral By 2050
node.description: The federal government's buildings and contracts for goods and services will be carbon neutral, and its fleet of cars and trucks will be all electric by 2050.

node.title: TN Medical Board Removes COVID Misinformation Policy From Web After GOP Backlash, Threats
node.description: "We have not rescinded our policy. Our charge is to protect the health and safety of the citizens of Tennessee," said Dr. Phyllis Miller said.

node.title: Sen. Richard Blumenthal Says Social Media 'Self-Policing' Has Failed, Calls for Oversight
node.description: "Self-policing depends on trust. The trust is gone," Senator Richard Blumenthal told Adam Mosseri during Wednesday's hearing on Capitol Hill.

node.title: Not a lot goes right for England on first day of Ashes
node.description: An insipid batting display lasting two sessions left England with a lot of catching up to do after a horror start to their Ashes campaign against Australia.

node.title: FDA Grants Emergency Authorization for COVID Prevention Drug for the Immunocompromised
node.description: The FDA stressed that the new monoclonal antibody therapy "is not a substitute for vaccination in individuals for whom COVID-19 vaccination is recommended."

node.title: In Daring Rescue, Crews Pull Unresponsive Woman From Car Suspended Above Niagara Falls
node.description: A rescuer, equipped with an ax, a yellow helmet, goggles and a snorkel, swayed to and fro in the wind as they tried to reach the submerged car.

node.title: Myanmar soldiers accused of 'horrific killing' after remains of 11 charred bodies are found
node.description: Soldiers are accused of rounding up 11 people in a village in central Myanmar and setting fire to their bodies, according to residents in the area and media reports.

node.title: More testing at Wainono Lagoon to find 'mystery' behind algae
node.description: Algae planktonic cyanobacteria has been discovered for the first time at the lagoon, giving it a green tinge and prompting a public health warning.

node.title: Man who found stacks of cash at Houston church gets $20,000 reward
node.description: "My heart stopped, needless to say," the plumber said after receiving a call about the gift.

node.title: Darlene Hard, Strong-Willed Tennis Star Before Pro Era, Dies at 85
node.description: Hard, who was outspoken and independent minded, was the top-ranked American woman from 1960 to 1963.

node.title: Frank Williams, Dominant Formula One Manager, Is Dead at 79
node.description: He overcame frequent adversity, including a near-fatal car accident, to become one of the most successful figures in motor sports history.

node.title: California Positions Itself as a ‘Refuge’ of Abortion Rights
node.description: A new legislative proposal includes the recommendation to fund the procedure for low-income women who come to California for abortion services.

node.title: The World Is Unprepared for the Next Pandemic, Report Says
node.description: The latest Global Health Security Index finds that no country is positioned well to respond to outbreaks.

node.title: U.S. Threat to Squeeze Russia’s Economy Is a Tactic With a Mixed Record
node.description: Sanctions, like aiming to cut oil exports, could also hurt European allies. “It’s a limited toolbox,” one expert said.

node.title: Less Than 1 Percent of LA School District Workers Fired for Not Complying With Vax Mandate
node.description: On Tuesday, the Los Angeles Unified School District's board moved to fire 496 of its approximately 73,000 workers.

node.title: Trial of Former Theranos CEO Elizabeth Holmes Heads to Recess, Closing Arguments to Come
node.description: The recess will last one week before closing arguments begin on December 16, three months after the trial began.

node.title: Queensland hits 80 per cent COVID vaccination milestone, but it's no 'Freedom Day'
node.description: The vaccination target for those 16 and over was reached more than a week early, however the state will not open its borders to hotpots until Monday.

node.title: Finnish PM sorry for going to nightclub after being exposed to COVID
node.description: After photographs of her night out appear in a Finnish gossip magazine, Sanna Marin admits she "did wrong" but claims she was told she didn't need to quarantine as she had been double-vaccinated.

node.title: Firefighters battle through the night to contain blaze still threatening lives and homes near Margaret River
node.description: An emergency warning remains in place for a bushfire that has been burning in the Margaret River region in Western Australia's South West since yesterday.

node.title: 'Privately issued money all too often ends in losses', RBA boss warns on crypto
node.description: Reserve Bank boss Philip Lowe again warns Australians to be cautious of investing in cryptocurrencies, including so-called stablecoins, noting that history shows "privately issued money all too often ends in losses for customers".

node.title: EBOS Group to buy medical equipment distributor in billion dollar deal
node.description: Diversified healthcare, medical and pharmaceutical products distributor EBOS Group has made a deal to buy medical equipment distributor LifeHealthcare for more than a billion dollars.

node.title: BusinessNZ refuses partnership role in Fair Pay Agreements policy
node.description: BusinessNZ has refused to be a formal partner in the government's showcase industrial policy, Fair Pay Agreements.

node.title: Man due in court on firearms-related charges after Ōtara incident.
node.description: A 40-year-old man is to appear in court on firearms charges after an incident in Ōtara.

node.title: Starbucks workers vote on union in upstate New York
node.description: Labor board rejects coffee chain's bid to stop the counting of ballots at three stores seeking to organize.

node.title: Stonewall Jackson, Grand Ole Opry Star for Over 60 Years, Dies at 89
node.description: His biggest record, “Waterloo,” topped the country music chart for five weeks in 1959 and became a crossover hit.

node.title: Greg Tate, Influential Critic of Black Culture, Dies at 64
node.description: His writing for The Village Voice and other publications helped elevate hip-hop and street art to the same planes as jazz and Abstract Expressionism.

node.title: The F.D.A. authorizes AstraZeneca drug to protect people with immune problems.
node.description: The antibody drug, Evusheld, was found to be strongly effective in preventing Covid in a clinical trial that enrolled mostly those at high risk.
